- At least what we can do, right?

1525
01:52:19,453 --> 01:52:24,186
<i>(Moore) Reggie was diagnosed with
pulmonary and bronchial problems.</i>

1526
01:52:24,257 --> 01:52:28,887
<i>The Cuban doctors gave her
a treatment plan to follow back home.</i>

1527
01:52:28,962 --> 01:52:32,398
<i>Along with some of those
five cent inhalers.</i>

1528
01:52:33,233 --> 01:52:37,067
<i>William Maher received a number
of treatments on his neck and his back.</i>

1529
01:52:37,137 --> 01:52:42,473
<i>Having ground down his teeth for
three years due to post-traumatic stress.</i>

1530
01:52:42,542 --> 01:52:45,443
<i>He left Cuba with a new set of teeth.</i>

1531
01:52:47,481 --> 01:52:51,542
<i>After a series of tests
on his heart. Lungs. Blood and stomach.</i>

1532
01:52:51,618 --> 01:52:54,280
<i>John now knew
what his ailments were.</i>

1533
01:52:54,354 --> 01:52:58,552
<i>He was given a strict plan to follow.
Plus a number of treatments</i>

1534
01:52:58,625 --> 01:53:01,992
<i>and was feeling better
than he had in years.</i>

1535
01:53:02,062 --> 01:53:07,125
<i>The Cuban doctors were able to take
Donna off five of her nine medications.</i>

1536
01:53:07,200 --> 01:53:11,136
<i>And with a correct diagnosis.
Gave her a treatment plan</i>

1537
01:53:11,204 --> 01:53:14,105
<i>to help her live a more normal life.</i>

1538
01:53:19,546 --> 01:53:21,810
<i>When firefighters
and paramedics in Havana</i>

1539
01:53:21,882 --> 01:53:24,544
<i>heard that the 911 rescue workers
were in town.</i>

1540
01:53:24,618 --> 01:53:27,883
<i>They invited them over
to one of their firehouses.</i>

1541
01:53:27,954 --> 01:53:30,218
<i>And so. On our last day there.</i>

1542
01:53:30,290 --> 01:53:32,986
<i>As we arrived. They stood at attention</i>

1543
01:53:33,059 --> 01:53:38,156
<i>because. They said.
They wanted to honor the heroes of 911.</i>

1544
01:54:16,236 --> 01:54:21,299
<i>S? Somos familia. Y los hermanos
que perdimos en las Torres Gemelas</i>

1545
01:54:21,374 --> 01:54:24,002
<i>se sinti?en el mundo completo.</i>

1546
01:54:25,178 --> 01:54:29,842
The brothers we lost on 9/11
was felt around the world.

1547
01:54:29,916 --> 01:54:32,510
<i>- Mis hermanos.
- Mis hermanos.</i>

1548
01:54:35,555 --> 01:54:38,251
Don't hesitate to hug a brother.

1549
01:54:43,196 --> 01:54:47,189
It's very important for them to wear
the SCBA so they don't end up like me.

1550
01:54:47,267 --> 01:54:49,701
- They're lungs.
- These tanks.

1551
01:54:49,769 --> 01:54:52,260
SCBA. Self-Contained
Breathing Apparatus.

1552
01:54:52,339 --> 01:54:55,467
<i>Tenemos una reserva tambin en el carro.</i>

1553
01:54:55,542 --> 01:54:57,669
<i>Es un placer poder venir aqu?</i>

1554
01:54:57,744 --> 01:55:00,474
<i>Esto es lo nico
que tenemos nosotros. . .</i>

1555
01:55:02,682 --> 01:55:05,014
F-F-F.

1556
01:55:05,085 --> 01:55:06,245
Three Fs.

1557
01:55:15,595 --> 01:55:19,292
<i>(Moore) If this is what can happen
beteen supposed enemies.</i>

1558
01:55:19,366 --> 01:55:23,268
<i>If one enemy can hold out his hand
and offer to heal.</i>

1559
01:55:23,336 --> 01:55:25,497
<i>Then what else is possible?</i>

1560
01:55:29,476 --> 01:55:32,036
<i>That's when I heard
that the man who runs the biggest</i>

1561
01:55:32,112 --> 01:55:34,876
<i>anti-Michael Moore website
on the internet</i>

1562
01:55:34,948 --> 01:55:37,781
<i>was going to have to shut it down.</i>

1563
01:55:37,851 --> 01:55:42,413
<i>He could no longer afford to keep it up
because his wife was ill</i>

1564
01:55:42,489 --> 01:55:46,755
<i>and they couldn't afford to pay
for her health insurance.</i>

1565
01:55:46,826 --> 01:55:52,822
<i>He was faced with a choice of either keep
attacking me or pay for his wife's health.</i>

1566
01:55:53,833 --> 01:55:56,734
<i>Fortunately. He chose his wife.</i>

1567
01:55:57,771 --> 01:56:02,071
<i>But something seemed wrong
about being forced into such a decision.</i>

1568
01:56:02,142 --> 01:56:06,442
<i>Why. In a free country. Shouldn't he
be able to have health insurance</i>

1569
01:56:06,513 --> 01:56:11,974
<i>and exercise his First Amendment right
to run me into the ground?</i>

1570
01:56:12,752 --> 01:56:17,189
<i>So I wrote a check for the $ 12.000
he needed to keep his wife insured</i>

1571
01:56:17,257 --> 01:56:21,387
<i>and in treatment.
And sent it to him anonymously.</i>

1572
01:56:23,663 --> 01:56:28,965
<i>His wife got better
and his website is still going strong.</i>

1573
01:56:34,808 --> 01:56:38,505
<i>It was hard for me to acknowledge
that in the end.</i>

1574
01:56:38,578 --> 01:56:40,842
<i>We truly are all in the same boat.</i>

1575
01:56:41,581 --> 01:56:44,277
<i>And that. No matter what our differences.</i>

1576
01:56:44,351 --> 01:56:47,377
<i>We sink or swim together.</i>

1577
01:56:47,454 --> 01:56:50,981
<i>That's how it seems to be
everywhere else.</i>

1578
01:56:51,558 --> 01:56:55,858
<i>They take care of each other.
No matter what their disagreements.</i>

1579
01:56:57,364 --> 01:57:02,961
<i>You know. When we see a good idea
from another country. We grab it.</i>

1580
01:57:03,036 --> 01:57:06,733
<i>If they build a better car. We drive it.</i>

1581
01:57:06,806 --> 01:57:10,139
<i>If they make a better wine. We drink it.</i>

1582
01:57:11,277 --> 01:57:14,508
<i>So if they've come up with
a better way to treat the sick.</i>

1583
01:57:14,581 --> 01:57:16,572
<i>To teach their kids.</i>

1584
01:57:17,650 --> 01:57:20,141
<i>To take care of their babies.</i>

1585
01:57:21,154 --> 01:57:24,055
<i>To simply be good to each other.</i>

1586
01:57:24,124 --> 01:57:26,752
<i>Then what's our problem?</i>

1587
01:57:26,826 --> 01:57:29,158
<i>Why can't we do that?</i>

1588
01:57:29,229 --> 01:57:32,687
<i>They live in a world of "we."
Not "me."</i>

1589
01:57:33,767 --> 01:57:38,704
<i>We'll never fix anything
until we get that one basic thing right.</i>

1590
01:57:38,772 --> 01:57:41,900
<i>And powerful forces
hope that we never do.</i>

1591
01:57:42,575 --> 01:57:46,306
<i>And that we remain the only country
in the western world</i>

1592
01:57:46,379 --> 01:57:49,371
<i>without free universal healthcare.</i>

1593
01:57:50,150 --> 01:57:54,143
<i>You know. If we ever did remove
the chokehold of medical bills.</i>

1594
01:57:54,754 --> 01:57:57,723
<i>College loans. Day care.</i>

1595
01:57:57,791 --> 01:58:01,955
<i>And everything else
that makes us afraid to step out of line.</i>

1596
01:58:02,028 --> 01:58:04,724
<i>Well. Watch out.</i>

1597
01:58:04,798 --> 01:58:08,325
<i>'Cause it'll be a new day in America.</i>

1598
